result.execSummary:
Michael B. Pena Kelly was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Michael B. Pena Kelly was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Waiver of extradition filed and distributed

Case called at 1:55 pm [Clerk SH]
Defendant Michael B. Pena Kelly in court, in custody. DA Susan Victoria Happ appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Date of birth and address confirmed accurate; Service of extradition complaint and commitment warrant admitted; reading waived
Mr. Pena Kelly informs the Court that he would like to waive extradition
Court reviews rights with Mr. Pena Kelly regarding extradition
Mr. Pena Kelly confirms that he would like to waive extradition
Court accepts the waiver and grants commitment, not to exceed 30 days
DA Happ submits waiver to Mr. Pena Kelly for endorsement and submits order to the Court
Court endorses orders & informs Mr. Pena Kelly that he will be held without bond
Recess: 2:03 pm
